{"word":"στείχω","slug":"στείχω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στείχω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to walk, march, go</i> or <i>come</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> loci, <i>to go to, approach</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to go after one another, go in line</i> or <i>order</i> (whence <el>στίχος, στίχες, στοῖχος</el>), <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>στ. ὁδόν</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}